members.name: getNodeName
members.comment: Returns the node name associated with this node.

return: the node name, as a String.

members.name: getNodeValue
members.comment: Returns the value associated with this node.

return: the node value, as a String.

members.name: setNodeValue
members.comment: Sets the String value associated with this node.

members.name: getNodeType
members.comment: Returns the node type, which is always ELEMENT_NODE.

return: the short value ELEMENT_NODE.

members.name: getParentNode
members.comment: Returns the parent of this node. A null value indicates that the node is the root of its own tree. To add a node to an existing tree, use one of the insertBefore, replaceChild, or appendChild methods.

return: the parent, as a Node.

members.name: getChildNodes
members.comment: Returns a NodeList that contains all children of this node. If there are no children, this is a NodeList containing no nodes.

return: the children as a NodeList

members.name: getFirstChild
members.comment: Returns the first child of this node, or null if the node has no children.

return: the first child, as a Node, or null

members.name: getLastChild
members.comment: Returns the last child of this node, or null if the node has no children.

return: the last child, as a Node, or null.

members.name: getPreviousSibling
members.comment: Returns the previous sibling of this node, or null if this node has no previous sibling.

return: the previous sibling, as a Node, or null.

members.name: getNextSibling
members.comment: Returns the next sibling of this node, or null if the node has no next sibling.

return: the next sibling, as a Node, or null.

members.name: getAttributes
members.comment: Returns a NamedNodeMap containing the attributes of this node.

return: a NamedNodeMap containing the attributes of this node.

members.name: getOwnerDocument
members.comment: Returns null, since IIOMetadataNodes do not belong to any Document.

return: null.

members.name: insertBefore
members.comment: Inserts the node newChild before the existing child node refChild. If refChild is null, insert newChild at the end of the list of children.

param: newChild - the Node to insert.
refChild - the reference Node.
return: the node being inserted.

members.name: replaceChild
members.comment: Replaces the child node oldChild with newChild in the list of children, and returns the oldChild node.

param: newChild - the Node to insert.
oldChild - the Node to be replaced.
return: the node replaced.

members.name: removeChild
members.comment: Removes the child node indicated by oldChild from the list of children, and returns it.

param: oldChild - the Node to be removed.
return: the node removed.

members.name: appendChild
members.comment: Adds the node newChild to the end of the list of children of this node.

param: newChild - the Node to insert.
return: the node added.

members.name: hasChildNodes
members.comment: Returns true if this node has child nodes.

return: true if this node has children.

members.name: cloneNode
members.comment: Returns a duplicate of this node. The duplicate node has no parent (getParentNode returns null). If a shallow clone is being performed (deep is false), the new node will not have any children or siblings. If a deep clone is being performed, the new node will form the root of a complete cloned subtree.

param: deep - if true, recursively clone the subtree under the specified node; if false, clone only the node itself.
return: the duplicate node.

members.name: normalize
members.comment: Does nothing, since IIOMetadataNodes do not contain Text children.

members.name: isSupported
members.comment: Returns false since DOM features are not supported.

param: feature - a String, which is ignored.
version - a String, which is ignored.
return: false.

members.name: getNamespaceURI

members.comment: Returns null, since namespaces are not supported.

name: javax.imageio.metadata.IIOMetadataNode
comment:
A class representing a node in a meta-data tree, which implements the org.w3c.dom.Element interface and additionally allows for the storage of non-textual objects via the getUserObject and setUserObject methods.

This class is not intended to be used for general XML processing. In particular, Element nodes created within the Image I/O API are not compatible with those created by Sun's standard implementation of the org.w3.dom API. In particular, the implementation is tuned for simple uses and may not perform well for intensive processing.

Namespaces are ignored in this implementation. The terms "tag name" and "node name" are always considered to be synonymous. Note: The DOM Level 3 specification added a number of new methods to the Node, Element and Attr interfaces that are not of value to the IIOMetadataNode implementation or specification. Calling such methods on an IIOMetadataNode, or an Attr instance returned from an IIOMetadataNode will result in a DOMException being thrown.
